27/09/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The three countries participating in a weekend conference on the future of Southeast Europe -- Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro -- adopted a joint declaration Sunday (26 September). 
The participants agreed that they had made progress in democratic reforms and normalisation of regional ties. 
They acknowledged, however, that several issues must be resolved to restore confidence and understanding. 
(HINA, HRT - 26/09/04)
